1
00:01:06,336 --> 00:01:10,778
=The Truth=

2
00:01:11,480 --> 00:01:14,200
=Episode 16=

3
00:01:14,200 --> 00:01:15,200
I've been waiting.

4
00:01:15,200 --> 00:01:17,041
Finally, I caught you today.

5
00:01:17,041 --> 00:01:17,920
I'm in a hurry.

6
00:01:17,920 --> 00:01:19,801
You poisoned my dog.

7
00:01:19,801 --> 00:01:21,000
What's going on, Liu?

8
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:21,840
No idea.

9
00:01:21,840 --> 00:01:23,721
Something about that lady's dog.

10
00:01:23,721 --> 00:01:26,041
Not sure why it's related
to the delivery guy.

11
00:01:26,041 --> 00:01:26,721
I grabbed you.

12
00:01:26,721 --> 00:01:27,560
Why the fuss?

13
00:01:27,560 --> 00:01:29,681
You're not making any sense.

14
00:01:29,920 --> 00:01:31,521
You two, back to work.
I'll check it out.

15
00:01:31,521 --> 00:01:31,961
Got it.

16
00:01:31,961 --> 00:01:33,360
You poisoned my dog.

17
00:01:33,360 --> 00:01:34,601
Of course, I have to grab you.

18
00:01:34,681 --> 00:01:35,280
Wait...

19
00:01:36,161 --> 00:01:37,161
You're lying!

20
00:01:37,161 --> 00:01:38,521
I'm swamped with deliveries.

21
00:01:38,521 --> 00:01:40,161
No time to poison your dog.

22
00:01:40,161 --> 00:01:42,041
Besides, I don't even see your dog.

23
00:01:42,041 --> 00:01:43,041
Stop pretending!

24
00:01:43,041 --> 00:01:44,560
You kicked my dog before.

25
00:01:44,560 --> 00:01:45,400
Right here.

26
00:01:45,400 --> 00:01:45,881
I...

27
00:01:45,881 --> 00:01:47,681
Don't think I forgot it.

28
00:01:47,681 --> 00:01:48,961
You're just lying!

29
00:01:49,241 --> 00:01:50,480
Let me go!

30
00:01:50,480 --> 00:01:51,241
I'm not letting go!

31
00:01:51,760 --> 00:01:54,801
You also tossed sausages
in the flowerbeds.

32
00:01:55,120 --> 00:01:56,081
I saw it

33
00:01:56,081 --> 00:01:57,241
with my own eyes.

34
00:01:57,241 --> 00:01:57,760
I...

35
00:01:58,360 --> 00:01:59,441
- I...
- And he hit me.

36
00:01:59,441 --> 00:02:00,721
- It wasn't me!
- You...

37
00:02:00,721 --> 00:02:01,120
What...

38
00:02:01,120 --> 00:02:02,041
Let go!

39
00:02:02,241 --> 00:02:03,400
Let me go!

40
00:02:06,161 --> 00:02:07,881
You're so mean!

41
00:02:07,961 --> 00:02:08,480
Hold on.

42
00:02:08,480 --> 00:02:09,841
He poisoned my dog!

43
00:02:09,841 --> 00:02:11,680
You get up first.

44
00:02:11,680 --> 00:02:13,480
- Let go!
- You get up first.

45
00:02:13,561 --> 00:02:15,561
Grab him! He poisoned my dog!

46
00:02:15,561 --> 00:02:16,360
Mr. Cao?

47
00:02:16,401 --> 00:02:17,920
- Poisoner!
- You...

48
00:02:21,200 --> 00:02:22,920
We investigated
Zhao Junxin's connections.

49
00:02:23,881 --> 00:02:26,281
She'd worked
for this housekeeping company for years,

50
00:02:26,281 --> 00:02:27,441
with great reviews.

51
00:02:28,601 --> 00:02:30,841
She was at the hospital that day,

52
00:02:31,161 --> 00:02:33,441
covering a shift for a colleague.

53
00:02:34,640 --> 00:02:35,401
By the way,

54
00:02:35,680 --> 00:02:38,001
the fruit knife she used

55
00:02:38,640 --> 00:02:41,640
was borrowed from a patient's family.

56
00:02:42,960 --> 00:02:44,800
How did Zhao Junxin learn

57
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:47,441
about Liao Guangyong
being at Central Hospital?

58
00:02:47,881 --> 00:02:49,121
She didn't explain.

59
00:02:50,121 --> 00:02:52,920
But Liao Guangyong's name
was on the hospital screen,

60
00:02:53,441 --> 00:02:55,240
visible to everyone passing by.

61
00:02:55,441 --> 00:02:56,520
It doesn't prove anything.

62
00:02:57,601 --> 00:03:03,321
So Zhao Junxin's attack was on impulse?

63
00:03:04,441 --> 00:03:06,760
That's what evidence suggests.

64
00:03:09,121 --> 00:03:10,360
Any other questions?

65
00:03:11,721 --> 00:03:14,401
This Zhao Junxin...

66
00:03:15,480 --> 00:03:16,200
Hard to say.

67
00:03:17,041 --> 00:03:21,841
I feel she's hiding something.

68
00:03:23,401 --> 00:03:25,041
Any progress on the poisoning case?

69
00:03:25,760 --> 00:03:29,121
We still can't rule out the possibility
Song Ying committed suicide with poison.

70
00:03:30,920 --> 00:03:33,401
If Song Ying didn't do it...

71
00:03:34,640 --> 00:03:36,441
Then it's Jiang Yuzhen.

72
00:03:51,920 --> 00:03:53,121
What's her story?

73
00:03:53,121 --> 00:03:53,960
She doesn't talk.

74
00:03:54,161 --> 00:03:55,721
I heard she's in for murder.

75
00:03:56,240 --> 00:03:57,161
Exactly.

76
00:03:57,321 --> 00:03:59,841
I heard two died on the spot.

77
00:04:01,520 --> 00:04:02,321
Two?

78
00:04:02,321 --> 00:04:03,200
How horrifying.

79
00:04:07,640 --> 00:04:08,881
Keep it down.

80
00:04:11,960 --> 00:04:13,640
Mr. Cao, sorry

81
00:04:13,800 --> 00:04:14,960
to cause you trouble.

82
00:04:14,960 --> 00:04:15,960
No problem.

83
00:04:16,440 --> 00:04:19,680
Resolving disputes is part of our duty.

84
00:04:20,041 --> 00:04:21,721
And you just wanted to help.

85
00:04:23,120 --> 00:04:26,800
Honestly, I assumed
it was really the delivery guy's doing.

86
00:04:27,041 --> 00:04:27,641
Well,

87
00:04:28,120 --> 00:04:29,560
without this commotion today,

88
00:04:29,560 --> 00:04:31,320
we wouldn't have caught the poisoner.

89
00:04:32,041 --> 00:04:33,360
What a wild coincidence.

90
00:04:33,641 --> 00:04:36,841
That delivery guy happened
to witness the poisoning.

91
00:04:37,120 --> 00:04:39,041
We retrieved the footage as he said.

92
00:04:39,120 --> 00:04:39,841
It caught him.

93
00:04:41,041 --> 00:04:41,920
Well, I wonder

94
00:04:42,281 --> 00:04:44,240
what that guy was thinking.

95
00:04:44,641 --> 00:04:47,560
He bought poison online
to kill dogs after job-hunting fails.

96
00:04:48,880 --> 00:04:49,880
I really don't get it.

97
00:04:51,560 --> 00:04:52,641
Sir, caught the suspect.

98
00:04:52,841 --> 00:04:54,120
Take him in. I'll be there.

99
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:54,761
Yes.

100
00:05:01,360 --> 00:05:02,680
This is the poisoner.

101
00:05:03,961 --> 00:05:04,800
Him?

102
00:05:06,880 --> 00:05:07,560
Jing.

103
00:05:07,761 --> 00:05:09,120
Then I won't see you out.

104
00:05:09,880 --> 00:05:11,120
Please go ahead.

105
00:05:31,841 --> 00:05:33,800
(Mom, I've applied for a transfer.)

106
00:05:35,641 --> 00:05:36,761
(It'll be approved soon.)

107
00:05:36,961 --> 00:05:39,401
(Then I can spend more time with you)

108
00:05:39,401 --> 00:05:40,472
(and eat your cooking.)

109
00:05:46,201 --> 00:05:48,000
Based on my examination, I can confirm

110
00:05:48,201 --> 00:05:50,000
the poison found at Jiang Yuzhen's house

111
00:05:50,201 --> 00:05:52,880
is the same as the one at the scene
and in the victim's body.

112
00:05:53,120 --> 00:05:57,081
Even the impurities mixed
in the chemicals are identical.

113
00:05:57,240 --> 00:06:00,281
That proves they are from
the same manufacturer and batch.

114
00:06:00,504 --> 00:06:03,521
Only Jiang Yuzhen's fingerprints were
found on both the poison's packaging

115
00:06:03,521 --> 00:06:05,721
and the inner side
of the suspended ceiling panel.

116
00:06:07,120 --> 00:06:09,240
Additionally, on the key to that safe,

117
00:06:09,601 --> 00:06:11,641
Jiang Yuzhen's fingerprints
were also detected.

118
00:06:13,320 --> 00:06:15,120
This old lady not only stole things,

119
00:06:15,120 --> 00:06:16,841
but also poisoned people?

120
00:06:17,240 --> 00:06:18,601
I never would've guessed.

121
00:06:19,041 --> 00:06:24,000
Fingerprints alone can only prove
Jiang Yuzhen touched this key.

122
00:06:24,641 --> 00:06:25,841
Any other evidence?

123
00:06:26,240 --> 00:06:27,641
Well, we...

124
00:06:27,880 --> 00:06:28,680
Play the video, Lei.

125
00:06:28,680 --> 00:06:29,680
Let's watch the video.

126
00:06:32,521 --> 00:06:33,720
Based on your understanding,

127
00:06:34,328 --> 00:06:36,401
does Song Ying
seem like the type to commit suicide?

128
00:06:36,641 --> 00:06:38,800
I can't say for sure.

129
00:06:56,800 --> 00:06:57,641
Wait.

130
00:06:58,120 --> 00:06:59,081
Rewind a bit.

131
00:07:02,521 --> 00:07:03,641
Look at her bag.

132
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:07,480
This is a bank giveaway, right?

133
00:07:07,480 --> 00:07:09,401
I seem to have an identical one.

134
00:07:09,560 --> 00:07:10,401
It's made of canvas,

135
00:07:10,401 --> 00:07:11,401
quite roomy.

136
00:07:12,560 --> 00:07:16,641
The bag looked different
when she entered and when she left.

137
00:07:17,761 --> 00:07:18,961
Indeed.

138
00:07:19,360 --> 00:07:20,800
It's not obvious at first glance.

139
00:07:21,320 --> 00:07:22,401
Look at her movements.

140
00:07:23,161 --> 00:07:25,320
When she entered,
she was carrying groceries.

141
00:07:25,920 --> 00:07:27,800
She carried the bag
on one shoulder with ease.

142
00:07:28,081 --> 00:07:29,761
But when she left,

143
00:07:30,521 --> 00:07:31,641
her shoulders and movements

144
00:07:31,841 --> 00:07:32,841
were tense.

145
00:07:33,641 --> 00:07:35,041
The bag had clearly gotten heavier.

146
00:07:36,120 --> 00:07:36,920
Well,

147
00:07:36,920 --> 00:07:39,000
her movements do seem a bit different.

148
00:07:40,360 --> 00:07:42,920
But could it be because of nervousness?

149
00:07:42,920 --> 00:07:45,240
After all, she just found
a dead body in the house.

150
00:07:45,680 --> 00:07:48,440
She must have put something in it.

151
00:07:49,240 --> 00:07:50,840
We knew that they kept
some cash at home,

152
00:07:50,840 --> 00:07:53,320
like a hundred thousand US dollars
and a hundred thousand RMB.

153
00:07:53,320 --> 00:07:54,320
She must put that in.

154
00:07:54,320 --> 00:07:56,000
And the watches and diamond rings,

155
00:07:56,641 --> 00:07:58,041
those are quite heavy.

156
00:07:58,761 --> 00:08:01,240
This old lady is bold!

157
00:08:01,761 --> 00:08:06,120
She basically moved the stolen goods
right under your nose.

158
00:08:06,800 --> 00:08:09,841
If Jiang Yuzhen is the one
who poisoned him,

159
00:08:10,120 --> 00:08:11,281
what's the motive?

160
00:08:12,401 --> 00:08:13,480
Just for the money?

161
00:08:14,641 --> 00:08:16,641
Jiang Yuzhen's family isn't well off.

162
00:08:16,641 --> 00:08:18,920
I think the motive of theft
is plausible.

163
00:08:19,880 --> 00:08:21,680
Her son doesn't seem
like a good guy either.

164
00:08:21,680 --> 00:08:22,841
He might be involved too.

165
00:08:30,041 --> 00:08:30,961
I can't run anymore.

166
00:08:33,281 --> 00:08:34,080
Little Qian.

167
00:08:34,881 --> 00:08:36,041
No more running.

168
00:08:36,481 --> 00:08:37,361
Buy some water.

169
00:08:38,001 --> 00:08:39,881
No more running.

170
00:08:40,200 --> 00:08:41,281
I won't run anymore.

171
00:08:41,881 --> 00:08:42,680
What?

172
00:08:44,281 --> 00:08:46,200
Two bottles of water.
Room-temperature. Thanks.

173
00:08:46,401 --> 00:08:46,881
Okay.

174
00:08:51,960 --> 00:08:52,881
Here you go.

175
00:08:53,481 --> 00:08:53,960
Thank you.

176
00:08:53,960 --> 00:08:54,560
Take care.

177
00:09:01,241 --> 00:09:05,281
I had a meal
with Little Zhao the other day.

178
00:09:08,680 --> 00:09:10,560
I had a meal
with Little Zhao the other day.

179
00:09:11,440 --> 00:09:12,840
She was crying so hard.

180
00:09:13,560 --> 00:09:15,361
She was pouring that sake

181
00:09:15,361 --> 00:09:17,800
into her mouth like crazy.

182
00:09:18,440 --> 00:09:19,960
After that, she dragged me to karaoke

183
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:20,960
and sang for two hours.

184
00:09:20,960 --> 00:09:22,361
What a torture.

185
00:09:22,920 --> 00:09:24,761
You two have been friends
for so many years.

186
00:09:24,761 --> 00:09:26,761
Can't you comfort her?

187
00:09:33,361 --> 00:09:34,840
Because we've been friends for long,

188
00:09:35,440 --> 00:09:36,521
I have no choice.

189
00:09:37,560 --> 00:09:40,161
The sooner she gives up on me,
the better it is for her.

190
00:09:41,560 --> 00:09:43,041
I know what you mean.

191
00:09:43,960 --> 00:09:45,361
But she is a girl.

192
00:09:45,401 --> 00:09:48,200
It's really hard to see her
like that, you know?

193
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:50,041
You like her
and want to pursue her, right?

194
00:09:50,481 --> 00:09:51,361
I have no choice.

195
00:09:51,440 --> 00:09:52,560
Neither do you?

196
00:09:55,361 --> 00:09:57,001
What are you talking about?

197
00:09:57,600 --> 00:09:59,401
Do you expect me
to take advantage of this?

198
00:10:01,041 --> 00:10:02,200
Alright, put that aside.

199
00:10:02,200 --> 00:10:03,401
How are you and your crush?

200
00:10:03,401 --> 00:10:04,361
How far have you gotten?

201
00:10:04,881 --> 00:10:06,641
When will you let me meet her?

202
00:10:13,440 --> 00:10:15,161
I won't run. I'll wait for you here.

203
00:10:19,161 --> 00:10:19,761
Sir.

204
00:10:20,161 --> 00:10:22,200
I used all my connections to ask around.

205
00:10:23,161 --> 00:10:24,960
Turn out that Lin from Provincial

206
00:10:26,800 --> 00:10:28,960
really is related to Ye Qian.

207
00:10:30,041 --> 00:10:32,200
With Huo's crew trying
to involve someone like that,

208
00:10:32,800 --> 00:10:36,401
they've planned
to exploit police connections.

209
00:10:37,281 --> 00:10:39,161
But from their conversation,

210
00:10:39,840 --> 00:10:41,560
I feel they actually don't know

211
00:10:41,560 --> 00:10:43,680
Ye Qian has this kind of connection.

212
00:10:44,001 --> 00:10:45,840
Well...

213
00:10:50,361 --> 00:10:53,001
Do you think someone like him
involving in willingly

214
00:10:54,840 --> 00:10:56,761
could be a setup or a trap?

215
00:10:58,041 --> 00:10:59,720
Ye Qian might be an undercover cop?

216
00:11:08,001 --> 00:11:09,281
We should test him.

217
00:11:10,641 --> 00:11:11,600
If he is,

218
00:11:12,680 --> 00:11:15,161
we cut all ties with Huo.

219
00:11:16,161 --> 00:11:17,161
If he isn't,

220
00:11:18,600 --> 00:11:21,041
then those guys have something
that valuable...

221
00:11:23,361 --> 00:11:24,161
What a pity!

222
00:11:26,641 --> 00:11:27,560
I'll arrange it.

223
00:11:31,401 --> 00:11:32,121
That's great.

224
00:12:17,848 --> 00:12:31,672
(Yunxi Central Hospital)

225
00:13:24,600 --> 00:13:26,161
She's a regular customer here.

226
00:13:26,161 --> 00:13:28,440
Works as a nursing aide
at a hospital, I think.

227
00:13:30,281 --> 00:13:31,361
Does she come often?

228
00:13:32,440 --> 00:13:33,800
Every few days.

229
00:13:33,881 --> 00:13:35,161
Usually around this hour.

230
00:13:35,161 --> 00:13:36,800
Because we have discounts now.

231
00:13:37,161 --> 00:13:38,521
What flowers does she buy?

232
00:13:39,481 --> 00:13:41,080
Like sunflowers,

233
00:13:41,080 --> 00:13:43,241
carnations, lilies, roses...

234
00:13:43,680 --> 00:13:45,080
Probably has kids at home.

235
00:13:45,440 --> 00:13:46,281
Why?

236
00:13:47,161 --> 00:13:48,800
I can tell you don't buy flowers often.

237
00:13:48,800 --> 00:13:49,840
The flowers I mentioned

238
00:13:49,840 --> 00:13:51,960
are more suitable for children.

239
00:13:51,960 --> 00:13:52,960
Blessings for kids.

240
00:13:54,361 --> 00:13:56,800
Did she come the night before last?

241
00:13:57,001 --> 00:13:58,041
The night before last?

242
00:13:58,761 --> 00:13:59,600
Yes, she did.

243
00:13:59,600 --> 00:14:00,720
And she bought flowers.

244
00:14:00,720 --> 00:14:02,281
But she didn't buy the discounted ones.

245
00:14:02,481 --> 00:14:04,241
She asked for premium packaging.

246
00:14:04,560 --> 00:14:06,881
Discounted flowers
just get wrapped in newspaper.

247
00:14:06,881 --> 00:14:08,720
Premium packaging costs extra.

248
00:14:09,680 --> 00:14:11,241
Do you know where she went

249
00:14:11,241 --> 00:14:12,041
after that?

250
00:14:12,960 --> 00:14:14,641
I really don't know.

251
00:14:14,641 --> 00:14:17,200
I think she took a taxi.

252
00:14:18,761 --> 00:14:19,440
Thank you.

253
00:14:19,440 --> 00:14:20,241
No problem.

254
00:14:41,161 --> 00:14:41,840
It's me.

255
00:14:42,840 --> 00:14:44,024
Get a surveillance footage.

256
00:14:45,960 --> 00:14:46,680
The flower shop's.

257
00:14:47,761 --> 00:14:48,761
Had dinner yet?

258
00:14:49,161 --> 00:14:50,361
Ordered takeout again?

259
00:14:51,320 --> 00:14:52,320
I ate.

260
00:14:52,320 --> 00:14:54,800
It's good. We've got
braised pork chops here.

261
00:14:55,200 --> 00:14:56,560
But not as good as yours.

262
00:14:57,440 --> 00:14:59,361
Cut back on that greasy food.

263
00:14:59,560 --> 00:15:01,560
Your cholesterol was high once.

264
00:15:02,761 --> 00:15:06,560
By the way, Mr. Cao called today.

265
00:15:07,361 --> 00:15:08,560
About the little puppy.

266
00:15:09,281 --> 00:15:12,161
That young guy confessed.

267
00:15:13,200 --> 00:15:15,840
Several families are going
to sue him for damages.

268
00:15:16,761 --> 00:15:19,720
Mr. Cao asked if we want to join them.

269
00:15:20,361 --> 00:15:21,200
What do you think?

270
00:15:21,560 --> 00:15:22,361
It's up to you.

271
00:15:24,761 --> 00:15:27,241
Mr. Cao said that guy's from
a single-parent home,

272
00:15:27,440 --> 00:15:28,960
not having a well-off family.

273
00:15:29,680 --> 00:15:31,200
He finally got into university,

274
00:15:31,481 --> 00:15:33,161
but couldn't find a job
after graduation.

275
00:15:33,680 --> 00:15:35,161
Seems like he's had it rough.

276
00:15:36,121 --> 00:15:38,560
Maybe we should just let him off?

277
00:15:39,128 --> 00:15:40,664
He was born in the Year of the Dragon,

278
00:15:40,960 --> 00:15:42,560
same age as our Hui.

279
00:15:43,600 --> 00:15:45,320
Okay. Whatever you say.

280
00:15:45,481 --> 00:15:46,001
I'll get...

281
00:15:46,001 --> 00:15:47,241
I have to go. Bye then.

282
00:16:20,361 --> 00:16:21,161
Sorry.

283
00:17:22,400 --> 00:17:23,041
Luo.

284
00:17:23,681 --> 00:17:24,640
Search over here.

285
00:17:32,241 --> 00:17:33,800
I've said it many times.

286
00:17:34,041 --> 00:17:35,481
About the poison you mention,

287
00:17:35,481 --> 00:17:37,160
I know nothing about it.

288
00:17:42,560 --> 00:17:44,080
My mom is the victim.

289
00:17:44,080 --> 00:17:45,080
The way you're acting

290
00:17:45,080 --> 00:17:47,001
is like we're the criminals.

291
00:17:54,040 --> 00:17:55,544
(Upstairs and Downstairs: Living Area
Inside and Outside the Courtyard: Scenic Area)

292
00:17:56,800 --> 00:17:57,880
Want to buy an apartment?

293
00:17:58,481 --> 00:18:00,281
No, just browsing.

294
00:18:00,600 --> 00:18:02,281
Someone handed it to me on the street.

295
00:18:02,281 --> 00:18:05,041
These flyers are everywhere nowadays.

296
00:18:05,201 --> 00:18:06,880
The location is good.
Why not consider it?

297
00:18:07,360 --> 00:18:08,521
No, can't afford it.

298
00:18:08,521 --> 00:18:09,640
These are all large units.

299
00:18:14,721 --> 00:18:15,640
Be thorough.

300
00:18:18,360 --> 00:18:21,481
What are you looking for?

301
00:18:23,448 --> 00:18:25,176
Liao Guangyong's place
had something stolen.

302
00:18:28,640 --> 00:18:30,080
What are you implying?

303
00:18:31,521 --> 00:18:32,761
You think my mom is a thief?

304
00:18:33,281 --> 00:18:34,721
You are slandering her.

305
00:18:34,721 --> 00:18:35,921
I'll call the inspector

306
00:18:35,921 --> 00:18:36,880
to report you.

307
00:18:37,840 --> 00:18:39,681
Please cooperate with our work.

308
00:18:41,160 --> 00:18:43,281
We're just eliminating
all possibilities.

309
00:18:44,400 --> 00:18:45,441
On the day of the crime,

310
00:18:45,961 --> 00:18:48,441
have you seen that canvas bag
your mother carried?

311
00:18:49,400 --> 00:18:50,481
N-No.

312
00:18:51,360 --> 00:18:52,160
Really?

313
00:18:55,512 --> 00:18:58,008
(Li Xin Insurance Company)

314
00:19:04,760 --> 00:19:05,816
(Li Xin Insurance Company)

315
00:19:10,880 --> 00:19:11,921
G-Go ahead.

316
00:19:37,921 --> 00:19:40,041
Zhao Junxin, talk.

317
00:19:43,441 --> 00:19:47,241
That night, you went to the intersection
of Xing'an Road and Longshan Avenue.

318
00:19:47,721 --> 00:19:50,761
The site of that traffic accident
eight years ago, right?

319
00:19:52,640 --> 00:19:54,721
You brought a very expensive bouquet
when you went.

320
00:19:55,360 --> 00:19:56,160
Sunflowers.

321
00:19:56,921 --> 00:19:59,761
And unusually, you asked
the florist for premium packaging,

322
00:20:00,201 --> 00:20:01,600
and even took a taxi.

323
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:04,001
After you got there,

324
00:20:04,001 --> 00:20:06,521
you stayed for about half an hour
before leaving by taxi.

325
00:20:07,640 --> 00:20:09,600
The driver remembers you quite clearly.

326
00:20:10,880 --> 00:20:13,441
Partly because you had him
run the meter while waiting,

327
00:20:13,441 --> 00:20:14,400
which cost you a lot.

328
00:20:15,360 --> 00:20:16,241
And partly

329
00:20:16,840 --> 00:20:18,840
because you were quite emotional
on the way back.

330
00:20:19,800 --> 00:20:21,600
The driver even offered you tissues.

331
00:20:26,400 --> 00:20:27,560
You often buy flowers,

332
00:20:28,184 --> 00:20:30,456
but that was your first time
going to the accident site

333
00:20:31,201 --> 00:20:33,400
since your divorce, correct?

334
00:20:36,120 --> 00:20:38,560
We spoke to the colleague
you swapped shifts with.

335
00:20:40,201 --> 00:20:41,201
According to her,

336
00:20:41,521 --> 00:20:43,281
she did have a family situation
at the time,

337
00:20:44,360 --> 00:20:47,201
but she didn't require
an immediate shift swap.

338
00:20:47,521 --> 00:20:50,840
You volunteered to take her shift.

339
00:20:51,560 --> 00:20:55,080
Additionally, that day you were caring
for a patient in the inpatient ward.

340
00:20:55,441 --> 00:20:58,320
You didn't pass through the lobby
with the electronic screen.

341
00:20:58,880 --> 00:21:00,400
And no one in the inpatient ward area

342
00:21:00,400 --> 00:21:02,840
knew Liao Guangyong
was brought in for emergency treatment.

343
00:21:04,521 --> 00:21:09,160
So did you really kill
Liao Guangyong on impulse?

344
00:21:14,360 --> 00:21:15,640
Do you have children?

345
00:21:24,921 --> 00:21:25,560
Hello.

346
00:21:26,400 --> 00:21:27,080
Master.

347
00:21:27,521 --> 00:21:29,160
Confirmed with the insurance company.

348
00:21:29,600 --> 00:21:32,441
Jiang Yuzhen has a major
accidental death policy in her name.

349
00:21:33,320 --> 00:21:35,600
The policyholder and insured
are Jiang Yuzhen.

350
00:21:35,721 --> 00:21:37,320
The beneficiary is Geng Tianchou.

351
00:21:38,001 --> 00:21:39,481
Once the insured passes away,

352
00:21:39,880 --> 00:21:43,120
the beneficiary gets the principal
plus two million in payout.

353
00:21:44,521 --> 00:21:45,921
Also, per the insurer's records,

354
00:21:46,521 --> 00:21:50,320
Geng Tianchou called
the claims hotline that very afternoon.

355
00:21:50,800 --> 00:21:52,201
That was shortly after the crime.

356
00:21:52,761 --> 00:21:54,400
No news leaked the information yet.

357
00:21:54,640 --> 00:21:56,640
Even before we contacted Geng Tianchou.

358
00:21:58,120 --> 00:22:01,800
So he knew Jiang Yuzhen
would meet her end that day.

359
00:22:02,560 --> 00:22:05,521
Jiang Yuzhen bought this policy
four months ago.

360
00:22:07,721 --> 00:22:09,320
The insurer just discovered

361
00:22:09,761 --> 00:22:11,400
that before taking out the policy,

362
00:22:11,400 --> 00:22:14,360
Jiang Yuzhen had a comprehensive checkup
at a top-tier hospital elsewhere.

363
00:22:14,560 --> 00:22:18,800
The checkup proved Jiang Yuzhen
had late-stage small cell lung cancer,

364
00:22:19,360 --> 00:22:20,961
and started metastasizing to her brain.

365
00:22:22,600 --> 00:22:24,952
The insurance company refuses to pay,
citing Jiang Yuzhen

366
00:22:25,336 --> 00:22:28,320
concealed pre-existing conditions
and suspected suicide insurance fraud.

367
00:22:29,281 --> 00:22:30,080
Master.

368
00:22:32,001 --> 00:22:33,560
I have a wild idea.

369
00:22:34,320 --> 00:22:35,120
Go on.

370
00:22:36,681 --> 00:22:40,761
Jiang Yuzhen and Zhao Junxin
were likely in cahoots.

371
00:22:58,320 --> 00:22:58,921
Buddy,

372
00:22:59,761 --> 00:23:01,160
just pour it in.

373
00:23:01,840 --> 00:23:02,441
Here.

374
00:23:16,921 --> 00:23:17,800
Enjoy.

375
00:23:17,800 --> 00:23:18,840
I do.

376
00:24:07,281 --> 00:24:07,921
Who are you?

377
00:24:08,201 --> 00:24:09,481
I'm looking for Han Zhao.

378
00:24:09,761 --> 00:24:11,160
Alright, I'll call her.

379
00:24:18,241 --> 00:24:19,521
What took you so long?

380
00:24:19,961 --> 00:24:21,521
I figured you hadn't eaten,

381
00:24:21,521 --> 00:24:23,241
so I grabbed you some food on the way.

382
00:24:23,800 --> 00:24:25,080
Who needs food? We're drinking.

383
00:24:25,080 --> 00:24:26,160
Come on, get in here!

384
00:24:28,320 --> 00:24:29,400
You're having a party?

385
00:24:29,521 --> 00:24:30,640
I don't know your friends.

386
00:24:30,640 --> 00:24:32,880
I'll give you the food and leave.

387
00:24:33,160 --> 00:24:33,921
You chicken out?

388
00:24:34,560 --> 00:24:35,360
Whatever.

389
00:24:36,041 --> 00:24:36,880
What should we play?

390
00:24:37,800 --> 00:24:38,721
I'm coming.

391
00:24:43,560 --> 00:24:44,600
Zhao, come play!

392
00:24:45,441 --> 00:24:46,521
Bottoms up!

393
00:24:46,521 --> 00:24:47,080
Okay.

394
00:24:47,576 --> 00:24:48,241
Go find a ma'am.

395
00:24:48,241 --> 00:24:49,961
I told you I could hold my liquor.

396
00:24:49,961 --> 00:24:50,600
Come on.

397
00:24:50,921 --> 00:24:52,201
It's rare we gather together...

398
00:24:52,721 --> 00:24:54,320
I'm not interested in you.

399
00:24:54,320 --> 00:24:55,761
We really can't hang out together.

400
00:24:55,761 --> 00:24:56,800
Let's open another bottle.

401
00:24:57,600 --> 00:24:58,961
We can hang out.

402
00:24:58,961 --> 00:24:59,400
Or...

403
00:25:01,840 --> 00:25:02,560
I can't anymore.

404
00:25:03,128 --> 00:25:04,768
(Little Zhaozhao
is throwing a party at home.)

405
00:25:04,768 --> 00:25:05,521
(Come check.)

406
00:25:05,521 --> 00:25:06,400
Cheers!

407
00:25:08,241 --> 00:25:08,961
Hurry!

408
00:25:08,961 --> 00:25:10,560
What a rare gathering!

409
00:25:11,640 --> 00:25:12,961
Come on, photographer!

410
00:25:13,320 --> 00:25:14,041
Here, drink.

411
00:25:14,281 --> 00:25:15,001
Drink.

412
00:25:15,800 --> 00:25:16,681
You two look good.

413
00:25:17,201 --> 00:25:17,840
(I'm at work. You guys have fun.)
Come on, bottoms up!

414
00:25:17,840 --> 00:25:18,481
Bottoms up!

415
00:25:18,521 --> 00:25:19,961
Finish it!

416
00:25:21,368 --> 00:25:23,098
(She's quite down. She drank a lot.)

417
00:25:23,098 --> 00:25:25,681
(Why don't you come over,
or give her a call to talk her down?)

418
00:25:25,681 --> 00:25:26,400
Okay?

419
00:25:34,880 --> 00:25:36,640
Everyone, cheers!

420
00:25:41,784 --> 00:25:45,208
(She knows her limits.
Letting it out is good for her.)

421
00:25:50,521 --> 00:25:51,600
Zhao, where are you going?

422
00:25:51,840 --> 00:25:52,640
Hold on a sec.

423
00:25:52,640 --> 00:25:53,281
Got it.

424
00:25:54,840 --> 00:25:55,640
Bored?

425
00:25:56,241 --> 00:25:57,041
No.

426
00:25:57,721 --> 00:25:58,961
Then why play on your phone?

427
00:26:00,001 --> 00:26:01,001
Just browsing.

428
00:26:02,441 --> 00:26:03,241
What's this?

429
00:26:04,080 --> 00:26:05,241
Brought you a gift.

430
00:26:05,320 --> 00:26:06,080
A game console.

431
00:26:07,640 --> 00:26:08,600
Quite expensive.

432
00:26:08,840 --> 00:26:10,041
Worth almost a month's salary.

433
00:26:11,921 --> 00:26:12,961
Come on, let's dance.

434
00:26:13,521 --> 00:26:14,080
No way.

435
00:26:14,400 --> 00:26:16,201
I'm all left feet.

436
00:26:16,201 --> 00:26:16,961
Your friends here.

437
00:26:16,961 --> 00:26:17,961
I'd embarrass you.

438
00:26:18,320 --> 00:26:19,521
You're my friend too.

439
00:26:19,521 --> 00:26:20,281
Come on.

440
00:26:20,400 --> 00:26:21,400
No.

441
00:26:21,921 --> 00:26:23,360
Drink less. It's bad for you.

442
00:26:25,241 --> 00:26:26,241
Then entertain yourself.

443
00:26:26,241 --> 00:26:26,880
Go have fun.

444
00:26:27,241 --> 00:26:28,041
How lame.

445
00:26:28,921 --> 00:26:29,800
I'm coming!

446
00:26:37,041 --> 00:26:40,560
Cheers!

447
00:26:54,640 --> 00:26:55,560
Another one!

448
00:27:13,656 --> 00:27:16,636
(Han Zhao: Transfer)

449
00:27:25,840 --> 00:27:26,560
Thanks.

450
00:27:34,761 --> 00:27:36,521
Stop looking. They didn't come.

451
00:27:43,400 --> 00:27:45,721
Have you thought about
what I said last time?

452
00:27:46,640 --> 00:27:47,681
Do you want my help?

453
00:27:49,160 --> 00:27:50,921
Want to go to Huashan in a few days?

454
00:27:51,961 --> 00:27:52,600
What for?

455
00:27:53,241 --> 00:27:54,400
Just hanging out.

456
00:27:56,001 --> 00:27:56,840
Just the two of us?

457
00:27:58,001 --> 00:27:59,721
What? Scared?

458
00:28:01,600 --> 00:28:02,761
Just the two of us is fine.

459
00:28:03,521 --> 00:28:05,048
If you're not scared, why would I be?

460
00:28:05,840 --> 00:28:06,961
Why want to go there?

461
00:28:08,281 --> 00:28:09,560
Why so many questions?

462
00:28:10,120 --> 00:28:11,521
I'll call you when I pick a day.

463
00:28:11,521 --> 00:28:12,041
Here.

464
00:28:17,241 --> 00:28:18,400
We're partners now.

465
00:28:18,400 --> 00:28:19,481
Won't accept my kindness?

466
00:28:24,840 --> 00:28:26,320
Nothing else in it today.

467
00:28:28,360 --> 00:28:29,400
I'm allergic to alcohol.

468
00:28:30,201 --> 00:28:30,921
Did you forget?

469
00:28:33,201 --> 00:28:34,921
He has an accelerated alcohol allergy.

470
00:28:34,921 --> 00:28:37,160
It caused laryngeal edema
and breathing difficulties.

471
00:28:37,201 --> 00:28:39,201
It could even be life-threatening.

472
00:28:41,281 --> 00:28:43,360
Luckily, he was brought in time.
No major issues.

473
00:28:45,160 --> 00:28:45,840
How lame.

474
00:28:51,320 --> 00:28:52,481
Call a designated driver.

475
00:28:53,120 --> 00:28:54,481
Let's go. No rush.

476
00:28:54,481 --> 00:28:56,080
Be careful. Don't trip here.

477
00:28:56,160 --> 00:28:56,560
Drunk?

478
00:28:56,560 --> 00:28:57,761
Not at all.

479
00:28:58,320 --> 00:28:59,041
You're drunk.

480
00:28:59,041 --> 00:28:59,800
Let's go.

481
00:29:00,041 --> 00:29:00,800
You had so much.

482
00:29:00,800 --> 00:29:01,560
Careful.

483
00:29:01,961 --> 00:29:03,080
Thank you.

484
00:29:03,281 --> 00:29:05,001
Bye! Text me when you get home.

485
00:29:05,001 --> 00:29:06,521
- Bye!
- Bye!

486
00:29:06,800 --> 00:29:07,521
Go home now.

487
00:29:07,521 --> 00:29:09,120
- I'll take her home. Don't worry.
- Okay.

488
00:29:09,120 --> 00:29:09,921
Bye.

489
00:29:10,800 --> 00:29:11,640
Bye.

490
00:29:27,921 --> 00:29:29,080
Why are you still here?

491
00:29:29,360 --> 00:29:30,600
I thought you went home.

492
00:29:30,880 --> 00:29:31,521
No.

493
00:29:32,441 --> 00:29:33,281
Are you hungry?

494
00:29:33,281 --> 00:29:34,560
Come to my place for a bite.

495
00:29:35,001 --> 00:29:35,681
No need.

496
00:29:35,961 --> 00:29:38,400
I wanted to chat with you.

497
00:29:38,640 --> 00:29:40,001
You had lots of friends around,

498
00:29:40,001 --> 00:29:41,241
so I waited for you here.

499
00:29:41,600 --> 00:29:43,241
What's there to chat?

500
00:29:47,120 --> 00:29:50,160
Aren't we friends?

501
00:29:51,201 --> 00:29:53,360
Transferring the money back
feels distant.

502
00:29:53,560 --> 00:29:54,241
Besides,

503
00:29:54,241 --> 00:29:55,840
you drink whenever you're down.

504
00:29:55,840 --> 00:29:56,721
That's bad for you.

505
00:29:57,041 --> 00:29:59,961
You can try to play some games instead.

506
00:30:00,241 --> 00:30:02,640
It'll soothe you.

507
00:30:02,640 --> 00:30:04,600
Or just imagine that guy is Little Qian.

508
00:30:04,721 --> 00:30:05,640
Vent it out.

509
00:30:09,281 --> 00:30:10,120
Thank you.

510
00:30:10,800 --> 00:30:11,481
I mean it.

511
00:30:13,840 --> 00:30:15,441
But I'm telling you for the last time,

512
00:30:16,041 --> 00:30:17,160
it won't work.

513
00:30:18,001 --> 00:30:18,800
Sorry.

514
00:31:07,201 --> 00:31:08,160
You're back.

515
00:31:21,001 --> 00:31:22,360
She finally came back.

516
00:31:25,001 --> 00:31:27,201
Don't end up getting yourself trapped.

517
00:31:28,320 --> 00:31:29,600
I know what I am doing.

518
00:31:31,600 --> 00:31:34,160
People have feelings.

519
00:31:34,521 --> 00:31:36,320
And no one can play with feelings.

520
00:31:36,800 --> 00:31:37,800
Do you know it?

521
00:31:39,721 --> 00:31:41,320
What's wrong with you today?

522
00:31:41,441 --> 00:31:43,800
You should ask
what's been wrong with you all along.

523
00:31:54,441 --> 00:31:55,441
What do you mean?

524
00:31:56,360 --> 00:31:56,961
Qing.

525
00:31:58,160 --> 00:32:00,400
Don't you see how jealous Huo is?

526
00:32:01,840 --> 00:32:02,761
Even I can tell.

527
00:32:19,600 --> 00:32:21,761
Fate really plays tricks on people.

528
00:32:24,721 --> 00:32:27,961
(Yunxi Zhenjiu Wine)
We've avoided each other for years.

529
00:32:31,640 --> 00:32:32,600
Never expected

530
00:32:36,400 --> 00:32:37,800
we'd still meet.

531
00:32:42,360 --> 00:32:43,160
Ye Qian.

532
00:32:48,761 --> 00:32:52,001
I know you...

533
00:33:05,880 --> 00:33:07,640
Remember.

534
00:33:11,840 --> 00:33:12,640
We owe

535
00:33:16,840 --> 00:33:18,521
nothing to each other.

536
00:33:22,921 --> 00:33:23,721
Sorry.

537
00:33:30,640 --> 00:33:32,120
Then I'm sorry too.

538
00:33:36,840 --> 00:33:38,001
How lame.

539
00:33:40,080 --> 00:33:43,320
Do you remember when we were kids?

540
00:33:45,800 --> 00:33:47,241
I said

541
00:33:49,721 --> 00:33:55,400
if you ever broke your word,

542
00:33:57,001 --> 00:33:58,400
I'd never talk to you.

543
00:33:59,840 --> 00:34:00,521
But

544
00:34:02,600 --> 00:34:05,281
today it suddenly hit me.

545
00:34:09,640 --> 00:34:11,200
I forgive you.

546
00:34:11,864 --> 00:34:17,976
♪After all, we've grown up
a bit these past few years♪

547
00:34:22,280 --> 00:34:23,321
I might

548
00:34:25,760 --> 00:34:27,160
drink too much.

549
00:34:33,013 --> 00:34:37,666
♪Do your best and don't let go♪

550
00:34:43,280 --> 00:34:46,640
I've been looking for you
all these years,

551
00:34:48,961 --> 00:34:49,760
Yumo.

552
00:34:53,432 --> 00:35:00,244
♪That so-called happiness
became pain without a place to land♪

553
00:35:00,244 --> 00:35:06,520
♪All the rights and wrongs
will fade away♪

554
00:35:08,280 --> 00:35:15,394
♪I really want to know
where you landed later♪

555
00:35:15,394 --> 00:35:21,988
♪So many words I've wanted to say,
yet I find myself speechless♪

556
00:35:22,360 --> 00:35:27,672
♪This world is too big,
but longing doesn't fear distance♪

557
00:35:27,672 --> 00:35:34,616
♪Make a wish upon a shooting star,
may it come true♪

558
00:35:34,616 --> 00:35:41,636
♪Perhaps I still can't let go
in my heart♪

559
00:35:41,672 --> 00:35:48,120
♪Time never lingers for love's sake♪

560
00:35:48,120 --> 00:35:52,473
♪But the world's complexity won't break♪

561
00:35:52,473 --> 00:35:58,808
♪I pray love's course remains true♪

562
00:36:00,248 --> 00:36:06,196
♪Wherever you are,
may happiness find you♪

563
00:36:06,648 --> 00:36:09,631
♪Remember this♪

564
00:36:14,481 --> 00:36:15,160
Master.

565
00:36:18,560 --> 00:36:20,321
I checked Zhao Junxin's phone.

566
00:36:20,600 --> 00:36:22,240
On the night
of the Fuquan Community case,

567
00:36:22,240 --> 00:36:25,361
she received this promotional text
from this number started with 150.

568
00:36:25,760 --> 00:36:27,841
At first glance, the text
was about selling property.

569
00:36:30,361 --> 00:36:32,001
"Fully renovated duplex apartments."

570
00:36:32,240 --> 00:36:33,881
"No purchase limits.
Mortgages available."

571
00:36:33,881 --> 00:36:36,720
"Contact number: 171..."

572
00:36:37,321 --> 00:36:38,841
Hold on, what's suspicious about that?

573
00:36:40,041 --> 00:36:41,881
I called this number.

574
00:36:41,881 --> 00:36:42,560
Void.

575
00:36:44,321 --> 00:36:47,080
Could they have just made a mistake

576
00:36:47,080 --> 00:36:48,640
when typing the number?

577
00:36:48,801 --> 00:36:51,961
These ads are usually
bulk-sent by software nowadays.

578
00:36:52,200 --> 00:36:53,640
I also tried calling

579
00:36:53,640 --> 00:36:54,881
the sender number.

580
00:36:54,881 --> 00:36:55,720
It's switched off.

581
00:36:55,720 --> 00:36:56,481
I checked.

582
00:36:56,640 --> 00:36:58,361
It's an unregistered number.

583
00:36:58,640 --> 00:37:01,841
This number sent Zhao Junxin
multiple texts before.

584
00:37:02,120 --> 00:37:03,720
The first was four months ago.

585
00:37:03,720 --> 00:37:05,240
Then, at regular intervals,

586
00:37:05,600 --> 00:37:09,160
it sent her different ad texts.

587
00:37:09,521 --> 00:37:11,560
About selling houses, selling cars,

588
00:37:11,560 --> 00:37:13,120
fake receipts, and so on.

589
00:37:13,120 --> 00:37:15,521
But they all listed
this same 171 number.

590
00:37:15,760 --> 00:37:17,921
We haven't found
Jiang Yuzhen's phone yet,

591
00:37:18,120 --> 00:37:20,001
but checking her call records

592
00:37:20,321 --> 00:37:25,401
showed this 150 number
also texted her multiple times.

593
00:37:28,361 --> 00:37:29,361
You think

594
00:37:29,441 --> 00:37:35,560
this is how Jiang Yuzhen
and Zhao Junxin communicated?

595
00:37:36,041 --> 00:37:36,680
Yes.

596
00:37:37,240 --> 00:37:38,481
Could it just be coincidence?

597
00:37:40,001 --> 00:37:41,280
I think that's impossible.

598
00:37:42,680 --> 00:37:45,200
Assuming they were connected,

599
00:37:45,961 --> 00:37:50,600
Zhao Junxin didn't have the opportunity
to poison Liao Guangyong and Song Ying.

600
00:37:51,240 --> 00:37:53,080
Jiang Yuzhen had motive
for insurance fraud.

601
00:37:54,041 --> 00:37:56,080
Suicide voids the insurance payout.

602
00:37:56,401 --> 00:37:58,001
To get the high payout,

603
00:37:58,160 --> 00:37:59,720
she needed an accident.

604
00:38:00,240 --> 00:38:03,521
You think it was a murder swap?

605
00:38:04,240 --> 00:38:08,321
Like in Strangers on a Train?

606
00:38:08,921 --> 00:38:10,841
You watched Hitchcock's movies?

607
00:38:12,600 --> 00:38:14,560
Looking down on me now?

608
00:38:15,001 --> 00:38:17,720
I've watched Hitchcock's and Conan's.

609
00:38:19,521 --> 00:38:22,841
If your theory holds,

610
00:38:24,120 --> 00:38:27,041
finding concrete proof
of their communication

611
00:38:27,521 --> 00:38:30,080
and collusion will be tough.

612
00:38:32,240 --> 00:38:33,441
Conquer them one by one.

613
00:38:33,760 --> 00:38:36,080
If they did it, there will be flaws.

614
00:38:36,321 --> 00:38:38,071
I've already asked Lei to track

615
00:38:38,071 --> 00:38:40,001
Geng Tianchou's movements
after the crime.

616
00:38:40,441 --> 00:38:43,720
Whether Geng Tianchou knows
their connection or not, he must know

617
00:38:43,961 --> 00:38:45,240
where the stolen goods are.

618
00:38:48,441 --> 00:38:51,441
You acted first and reported later.

619
00:38:53,441 --> 00:38:55,881
Don't alert the suspect!

620
00:38:57,401 --> 00:38:58,160
Don't worry.

621
00:39:05,600 --> 00:39:06,481
Hello, sir.

622
00:39:07,160 --> 00:39:07,401
Hello.

623
00:39:07,401 --> 00:39:09,080
We're from the Yunxi Police Department.

624
00:39:09,280 --> 00:39:10,361
Here are our badges.

625
00:39:11,080 --> 00:39:12,881
We'd like to ask you a few questions.

626
00:39:13,640 --> 00:39:14,280
Okay.

627
00:39:16,521 --> 00:39:18,240
Do you recognize
the person in this photo?

628
00:39:19,961 --> 00:39:22,080
This one seems familiar.
I gave him a ride.

629
00:39:22,160 --> 00:39:22,921
Right.

630
00:39:23,441 --> 00:39:24,321
When did that happen?

631
00:39:24,321 --> 00:39:25,240
Let me think.

632
00:39:25,640 --> 00:39:26,481
Three days ago.

633
00:39:27,720 --> 00:39:28,961
Morning, evening, or afternoon?

634
00:39:28,961 --> 00:39:29,841
Five in the afternoon.

635
00:39:30,521 --> 00:39:31,680
Took him to Wanda Plaza.

636
00:39:31,801 --> 00:39:32,921
Yes, Wanda Plaza.

637
00:39:43,280 --> 00:39:45,321
Remember what this person said to you?

638
00:39:45,841 --> 00:39:48,200
He asked me some questions
about deposits,

639
00:39:48,200 --> 00:39:50,168
but he didn't conduct
any specific transactions.

640
00:39:50,881 --> 00:39:51,320
Why?

641
00:39:51,320 --> 00:39:52,856
Per the new regulations from the bank,

642
00:39:53,016 --> 00:39:55,161
for cash transactions over 50,000 yuan
at the counter,

643
00:39:55,161 --> 00:39:56,921
the source and purpose must be reported.

644
00:39:56,961 --> 00:39:59,600
He seemed to not quite understand
this regulation.

645
00:40:00,160 --> 00:40:02,321
He also asked about
foreign currency deposits.

646
00:40:02,361 --> 00:40:03,841
I told him those also require report.

647
00:40:03,841 --> 00:40:05,080
Then he left.

648
00:40:12,001 --> 00:40:13,120
Let me show you some others.

649
00:40:13,120 --> 00:40:14,456
Buildings are too close.

650
00:40:14,921 --> 00:40:16,640
It's up to you.
I don't have the final say.

651
00:40:17,441 --> 00:40:18,200
This one.

652
00:40:19,521 --> 00:40:20,881
Have you seen this person?

653
00:40:22,401 --> 00:40:23,441
Well...

654
00:40:25,200 --> 00:40:26,481
I think I have some impression.

655
00:40:26,921 --> 00:40:28,280
He came here before.

656
00:40:28,680 --> 00:40:29,881
He came by himself.

657
00:40:31,600 --> 00:40:32,160
Yes.

658
00:40:32,401 --> 00:40:35,321
I remember he asked you
about small units.

659
00:40:35,841 --> 00:40:37,321
Then he changed to a large unit.

660
00:40:37,640 --> 00:40:38,441
When?

661
00:40:39,200 --> 00:40:41,240
Last Saturday, in the morning.

662
00:40:41,441 --> 00:40:43,080
He also asked us for some materials.

663
00:40:59,200 --> 00:41:00,041
We meet again.

664
00:41:02,961 --> 00:41:05,521
You know why we want to see you, right?

665
00:41:09,760 --> 00:41:10,560
Let's chat.

666
00:41:12,200 --> 00:41:15,041
Let's chat about the car accident
from that year.

667
00:41:17,001 --> 00:41:20,080
T-This was many years ago.

668
00:41:20,640 --> 00:41:21,881
Why are you asking about it?

669
00:41:21,881 --> 00:41:23,041
I know.

670
00:41:23,041 --> 00:41:24,041
It's been many years.

671
00:41:24,041 --> 00:41:25,680
So I said let's chat.

672
00:41:27,280 --> 00:41:28,441
Just a casual chat.

673
00:41:29,481 --> 00:41:31,200
Say whatever you remember.

674
00:41:31,200 --> 00:41:31,801
Relax.

675
00:41:32,441 --> 00:41:33,240
Okay.

676
00:41:35,401 --> 00:41:37,680
It happened a long time ago.

677
00:41:38,401 --> 00:41:42,921
As for many details,
I don't remember clearly.

678
00:41:43,760 --> 00:41:45,200
So,

679
00:41:45,321 --> 00:41:46,720
just say whatever you remember.

680
00:41:48,961 --> 00:41:53,680
The victim claimed 500,000 yuan.

681
00:41:54,600 --> 00:41:57,961
Seems like Liao Guangyong
paid it for you, right?

682
00:41:58,120 --> 00:41:59,961
No, I borrowed it.

683
00:42:01,240 --> 00:42:02,041
Borrowed it?

684
00:42:02,481 --> 00:42:03,280
Did you pay it back?

685
00:42:04,640 --> 00:42:05,361
No.

686
00:42:06,240 --> 00:42:07,720
And the transfer records.

687
00:42:08,160 --> 00:42:10,521
The money was transferred
several times, right?

688
00:42:12,321 --> 00:42:14,720
What do you think we do for a living?

689
00:42:15,881 --> 00:42:18,841
It's easy for us police to find out.

690
00:42:22,448 --> 00:42:25,941
♪Replacing the weight of tears
with that of sweat♪

691
00:42:29,735 --> 00:42:35,056
♪Covering the gunshot's sound
with wounds♪

692
00:42:37,129 --> 00:42:41,983
♪No one is born unyielding and strong♪

693
00:42:42,789 --> 00:42:45,936
♪But because someone
always rushes ahead♪

694
00:42:45,936 --> 00:42:49,040
♪To shield us from the storm♪

695
00:42:51,696 --> 00:42:56,830
♪When every extraordinary act
becomes routine♪

696
00:42:58,800 --> 00:43:04,432
♪Just to polish the badge
upon their shoulder♪

697
00:43:06,192 --> 00:43:09,776
♪Like light surging unseen
through the night♪

698
00:43:10,928 --> 00:43:18,368
♪Converging into your form♪

699
00:43:18,800 --> 00:43:21,478
♪Looking up♪

700
00:43:21,478 --> 00:43:25,017
♪Such dazzling glory♪

701
00:43:26,000 --> 00:43:28,560
♪Like hope♪

702
00:43:28,560 --> 00:43:32,493
♪Reaching out its arms♪

703
00:43:33,360 --> 00:43:36,012
♪Cloaked in light♪

704
00:43:36,012 --> 00:43:40,496
♪Alone, they charge ahead♪

705
00:43:40,496 --> 00:43:43,312
♪Traversing♪

706
00:43:43,312 --> 00:43:49,823
♪The battlefield of fate♪
